title: Marianna Tolvanen
text:
Marianna Tolvanen (born 27 December 1992) is a <a href="Finland">Finnish</a> <a href="women%27s%20soccer">football</a>er currently playing for <a href="FC%20Honka%20%28women%29">FC Honka</a> in the <a href="Naisten%20Liiga">Naisten Liiga</a>. She is also a member of the <a href="Finland%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Finnish national team</a> since 2011.
Tolvanen started her career in Honka. In 2011, she moved to <a href="HJK%20Helsinki%20%28women%29">HJK Helsinki</a>, where she was the 2011 season's second top scorer with 17 goals. In 2013, she returned to Honka.
In June 2013 Tolvanen was named in national <a href="Coach%20%28sports%29">coach</a> <a href="Andr%C3%A9e%20Jeglertz">Andrée Jeglertz</a>'s Finland squad for <a href="UEFA%20Women%27s%20Euro%202013">UEFA Women's Euro 2013</a>.
